> Our Creamy Cajun Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the ravioli.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper and fry until just soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks.

Stir in the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry for ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil, then simmer.

Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%milliliters} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts) to the pepper pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat. Stir in the @butter{20%grams} (see pantry for amount) and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} until melted.

Gently stir the cooked ravioli into the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the creamy Cajun ravioli between your #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%grams} leaves. Drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%milliliters} to finish.

Enjoy!